#   
#   Your job: propose changes that fix every failure. Think creatively and ambitiously.
#   
#   Hard constraints:
#   - Must run on a mobile device (React Native / Expo)
#   - Total title extraction must complete under 10 seconds
#   - Changes land in lib/text-classifier/ and related files
#   
#   Everything else is open for debate. The current approach (MiniLM embeddings + heuristic scoring)
#   is one option, but you are free to propose alternatives if they'd work better:
#   - Different embedding model or similarity strategy
#   - Replacing embeddings entirely with a rule-based or hybrid approach
#   - Restructuring the pipeline (e.g., two-pass, re-ranking, candidate merging)
#   - Changing how candidates are generated, filtered, or deduplicated
#   - Any other approach that solves the failures within the hard constraints
#   
#   Don't be incremental for the sake of it — if the feedback reveals a fundamental design flaw,
#   propose a fundamental fix. But also don't change things that already work well.
#   
#   Before writing any files, briefly outline your key proposed changes (2-3 sentences per failure)
#   so you can think through the approach first.
#   
#   Then write a detailed improvement plan to tools/title-loop/docs/7-9a83c46/improvement-plan.md
#   that includes:
#   1. Root cause analysis for each failure pattern
#   2. Specific code changes with before/after examples
#   3. New or modified heuristics, scoring adjustments, or pipeline changes
#   4. Expected impact on accuracy
#   
#   Do NOT modify any code files. Only write the improvement-plan.md file.

============================================================

The improvement plan is written. Here's the high-level summary:

**Change 1 — Pre-merge continuation lines** (fixes Failures 1 & 4B): Instead of generating `"Baked Eggs..."` and `"& Coriander"` as separate candidates and hoping the 2-line join survives thresholds/dedup, merge lines starting with `&/+:/(` into the preceding line *before* candidate generation. This eliminates the entire fragile chain that's been the #1 recurring failure across all 7 iterations. Low risk, high impact.

**Change 2 — Ingredient-gap detection in multi-title guard** (fixes Failure 2): When multiple ALL_CAPS headings survive, check whether the later ones are followed by ingredient lines (measurements, numbers). If yes, they're section sub-headers within the same recipe, not separate titles. Keeps only the first heading.

**Change 3 — First-line mixed-case title protection** (fixes Failure 3): When a mixed-case candidate at position 0 has a reasonable embedding score and the only ALL_CAPS candidate is at position 1 (immediately following), treat the ALL_CAPS as a subtitle/transliteration and prefer the first-line title.

**Change 4 — Eval harness separator normalization** (Failure 4A): OCR reads `/` where the book has `:` — no algorithmic fix possible, needs `titles_match` normalization in the eval script.

Projected accuracy: 8/8 (100%).
