{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AmZQhBfeFpAYKno3fhVLiV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#!/usr/bin/env python3\n     2→\"\"\"\n     3→Self-improving title extraction loop.\n     4→\n     5→Iteratively evaluates and improves the title extraction algorithm by:\n     6→1. Running extraction against real and generated OCR input files\n     7→2. Using Claude Code headless for analysis, planning, and implementation\n     8→3. Committing improvements and tracking accuracy across iterations\n     9→\n    10→Fully resumable: detects which step of an iteration was last completed\n    11→and picks up from there.\n    12→\n    13→Usage: python3 tools/title-loop/title-loop.py\n    14→\"\"\"\n    15→\n    16→import glob\n    17→import json\n    18→import os\n    19→import re\n    20→import shutil\n    21→import subprocess\n    22→import sys\n    23→import threading\n    24→import time\n    25→from pathlib import Path\n    26→\n    27→# --- Configuration ---\n    28→MAX_ITERATIONS = 20\n    29→ACCURACY_THRESHOLD = 0.95  # \"close to 100%\"\n    30→SYNTHETIC_COUNT = 100\n    31→CLAUDE_TIMEOUT = 900  # 15 minutes per Claude invocation\n    32→CLAUDE_STALL_TIMEOUT = 60  # kill if no output for N seconds (default)\n    33→CLAUDE_STALL_TIMEOUT_BY_MODEL = {\"opus\": 180, \"sonnet\": 120, \"haiku\": 60}\n    34→CLAUDE_MAX_RETRIES = 3  # max retries per stage on stall/failure\n    35→EXTRACT_TIMEOUT = 120  # 2 minutes per file extraction\n    36→\n    37→PROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent.parent\n    38→LOOP_DIR = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n    39→INPUT_DIR = LOOP_DIR / \"input\"\n    40→DOCS_DIR = LOOP_DIR / \"docs\"\n    41→EXTRACT_SCRIPT = LOOP_DIR / \"extract-title.ts\"\n    42→ITER_LOG = DOCS_DIR / \"iter.txt\"\n    43→\n    44→# Number of recent output lines to show in live display\n    45→\n    46→\n    47→# --- Resume state detection ---\n    48→\n    49→def find_iter_dir(iteration: int) -> Path | None:\n    50→    \"\"\"Find the iteration directory for a given iteration number (hash may vary).\"\"\"\n    51→    matches = sorted(DOCS_DIR.glob(f\"{iteration}-*\"))\n    52→    matches = [m for m in matches if re.match(rf\"^{iteration}-[a-f0-9]+$\", m.name)]\n    53→    return matches[0] if matches else None\n    54→\n    55→\n    56→def get_logged_accuracy(iteration: int) -> float | None:\n    57→    \"\"\"Read the accuracy logged for a specific iteration from iter.txt.\"\"\"\n    58→    if not ITER_LOG.exists():\n    59→        return None\n    60→    for line in ITER_LOG.read_text().strip().splitlines():\n    61→        m = re.match(r\"^(\\d+)\\s*-\\s*([\\d.]+)%\", line)\n    62→        if m and int(m.group(1)) == iteration:\n    63→            return float(m.group(2)) / 100\n    64→    return None\n    65→\n    66→\n    67→def get_last_logged_iteration() -> int:\n    68→    \"\"\"Read iter.txt to find the last logged iteration number. Returns 0 if none.\"\"\"\n    69→    if not ITER_LOG.exists():\n    70→        return 0\n    71→    last = 0\n    72→    for line in ITER_LOG.read_text().strip().splitlines():\n    73→        m = re.match(r\"^(\\d+)\\s*-\\s*\", line)\n    74→        if m:\n    75→            last = int(m.group(1))\n    76→    return last\n    77→\n    78→\n    79→def determine_resume_phase(iteration: int) -> str:\n    80→    \"\"\"\n    81→    Determine what phase to resume from for a given iteration.\n    82→\n    83→    Returns one of:\n    84→      'evaluate'  — no results yet, start from scratch\n    85→      'analyze'   — results exist but no feedback.md\n    86→      'plan'      — feedback exists but no improvement-plan.md\n    87→      'execute'   — plan exists but not yet implemented/committed\n    88→      'done'      — accuracy met threshold, iteration complete\n    89→    \"\"\"\n    90→    iter_dir = find_iter_dir(iteration)\n    91→    if iter_dir is None or not (iter_dir / \"results.txt\").exists():\n    92→        return \"evaluate\"\n    93→\n    94→    accuracy = get_logged_accuracy(iteration)\n    95→    if accuracy is not None and accuracy >= ACCURACY_THRESHOLD:\n    96→        return \"done\"\n    97→\n    98→    if not (iter_dir / \"feedback.md\").exists():\n    99→        return \"analyze\"\n   100→\n   101→    if not (iter_dir / \"improvement-plan.md\").exists():\n   102→        return \"plan\"\n   103→\n   104→    if (iter_dir / \"committed\").exists():\n   105→        return \"done\"\n   106→\n   107→    return \"execute\"\n   108→\n   109→\n   110→# --- Core helpers ---\n   111→\n   112→def normalize(s: str) -> str:\n   113→    \"\"\"Normalize whitespace and case for comparison.\"\"\"\n   114→    return \" \".join(s.lower().split())\n   115→\n   116→\n   117→def normalize_separators(s: str) -> str:\n   118→    \"\"\"Normalize filesystem-substituted characters (: replaces / in filenames).\"\"\"\n   119→    return s.replace(\":\", \"/\")\n   120→\n   121→\n   122→def titles_match(extracted: str, expected: str) -> bool:\n   123→    \"\"\"\n   124→    Binary match: does the extracted title contain all expected title parts?\n   125→    Expected may contain multiple titles separated by '+'.\n   126→    \"\"\"\n   127→    if not extracted:\n   128→        return False\n   129→    extracted_norm = normalize_separators(normalize(extracted))\n   130→    expected_parts = [normalize_separators(normalize(p)) for p in expected.split(\"+\")]\n   131→    return all(part in extracted_norm for part in expected_parts)\n   132→\n   133→\n   134→def extract_expected_title(filename: str) -> str:\n   135→    \"\"\"Extract expected title from filename like 'Tomato Soup.real.txt'.\"\"\"\n   136→    name = Path(filename).name\n   137→    cleaned = re.sub(r\"\\.(real|generated\\.\\d+)\\.txt$\", \"\", name)\n   138→    if cleaned == name:\n   139→        raise ValueError(f\"Unrecognized filename format: {filename!r}\")\n   140→    return cleaned\n   141→\n   142→\n   143→def run_extraction(file_path: str) -> str:\n   144→    \"\"\"Run the title extraction CLI on a file and return the extracted title.\"\"\"\n   145→    try:\n   146→        result = subprocess.run(\n   147→            [\"npx\", \"tsx\", str(EXTRACT_SCRIPT), file_path],\n   148→            capture_output=True,\n   149→            text=True,\n   150→            timeout=EXTRACT_TIMEOUT,\n   151→            cwd=str(PROJECT_ROOT),\n   152→        )\n   153→        if result.returncode != 0:\n   154→            print(f\"  WARNING: extraction failed for {file_path}: {result.stderr.strip()}\")\n   155→            return \"\"\n   156→        return result.stdout.strip()\n   157→    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n   158→        print(f\"  WARNING: extraction timed out for {file_path}\")\n   159→        return \"\"\n   160→\n   161→\n   162→def evaluate_files(file_paths: list[str]) -> list[dict]:\n   163→    \"\"\"Evaluate extraction on a list of files. Returns list of result dicts.\"\"\"\n   164→    results = []\n   165→    for fp in file_paths:\n   166→        expected = extract_expected_title(fp)\n   167→        extracted = run_extraction(fp)\n   168→        match = titles_match(extracted, expected)\n   169→        results.append({\n   170→            \"file\": fp,\n   171→            \"expected\": expected,\n   172→            \"extracted\": extracted,\n   173→            \"match\": match,\n   174→        })\n   175→        status = \"YES\" if match else \"NO\"\n   176→        print(f\"  {status}: expected='{expected}' got='{extracted}'\")\n   177→    return results\n   178→\n   179→\n   180→def compute_accuracy(results: list[dict]) -> float:\n   181→    \"\"\"Compute accuracy as fraction of matches.\"\"\"\n   182→    if not results:\n   183→        return 0.0\n   184→    return sum(1 for r in results if r[\"match\"]) / len(results)\n   185→\n   186→\n   187→def write_results(iter_dir: Path, results: list[dict]) -> None:\n   188→    \"\"\"Write results.txt with one line per file.\"\"\"\n   189→    iter_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n   190→    with open(iter_dir / \"results.txt\", \"w\") as f:\n   191→        for r in results:\n   192→            status = \"yes\" if r[\"match\"] else \"no\"\n   193→            f.write(f\"{r['expected']} - {status}\\n\")\n   194→\n   195→\n   196→def load_results_from_file(iter_dir: Path) -> list[dict]:\n   197→    \"\"\"Reconstruct minimal results from results.txt for building failure prompts.\"\"\"\n   198→    results = []\n   199→    results_path = iter_dir / \"results.txt\"\n   200→    if not results_path.exists():\n   201→        return results\n   202→    for line in results_path.read_text().strip().splitlines():\n   203→        m = re.match(r\"^(.+) - (yes|no)$\", line)\n   204→        if m:\n   205→            expected = m.group(1)\n   206→            match = m.group(2) == \"yes\"\n   207→            real_file = INPUT_DIR / f\"{expected}.real.txt\"\n   208→            file_path = str(real_file) if real_file.exists() else f\"(input file for '{expected}')\"\n   209→            results.append({\n   210→                \"file\": file_path,\n   211→                \"expected\": expected,\n   212→                \"extracted\": \"(from previous evaluation)\",\n   213→                \"match\": match,\n   214→            })\n   215→    return results\n   216→\n   217→\n   218→def get_commit_hash() -> str:\n   219→    \"\"\"Get current git commit hash (short).\"\"\"\n   220→    result = subprocess.run(\n   221→        [\"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"--short\", \"HEAD\"],\n   222→        capture_output=True,\n   223→        text=True,\n   224→        cwd=str(PROJECT_ROOT),\n   225→    )\n   226→    return result.stdout.strip()\n   227→\n   228→\n   229→def git_commit_all(message: str) -> str:\n   230→    \"\"\"Stage source changes and iteration docs. Returns new commit hash.\"\"\"\n   231→    subprocess.run(\n   232→        [\"git\", \"add\",\n   233→         \"lib/text-classifier/\",\n   234→         \"tools/title-loop/docs/\",\n   235→         \"tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts\",\n   236→         \"tools/title-loop/title-loop.py\"],\n   237→        cwd=str(PROJECT_ROOT),\n   238→        check=True,\n   239→    )\n   240→    # Temporarily disable Entire hooks to avoid interactive /dev/tty prompts\n   241→    subprocess.run([\"entire\", \"disable\"], cwd=str(PROJECT_ROOT),\n   242→                   capture_output=True)\n   243→    try:\n   244→        subprocess.run(\n   245→            [\"git\", \"commit\", \"-m\", message],\n   246→            cwd=str(PROJECT_ROOT),\n   247→            check=True,\n   248→        )\n   249→        return get_commit_hash()\n   250→    finally:\n   251→        subprocess.run([\"entire\", \"enable\", \"--agent\", \"claude-code\"],\n   252→                       cwd=str(PROJECT_ROOT), capture_output=True)\n   253→\n   254→\n   255→# --- Claude invocation with live display ---\n   256→\n   257→def _clear_display(height: int) -> None:\n   258→    \"\"\"Move cursor up and clear lines to overwrite previous display.\"\"\"\n   259→    if height > 0:\n   260→        sys.stdout.write(f\"\\033[{height}A\")\n   261→        for _ in range(height):\n   262→            sys.stdout.write(\"\\033[2K\\n\")\n   263→        sys.stdout.write(f\"\\033[{height}A\")\n   264→\n   265→\n   266→def _render_display(model: str, elapsed: float,\n   267→                    input_tokens: int = 0, output_tokens: int = 0) -> int:\n   268→    \"\"\"Render the live display line. Returns number of lines written.\"\"\"\n   269→    term_width = shutil.get_terminal_size().columns\n   270→\n   271→    header = f\"  Running Claude ({model})...\"\n   272→    stats = f\"\\u2191 {input_tokens:,} | \\u2193 {output_tokens:,} | {elapsed:.0f}s\"\n   273→    padding = max(1, term_width - len(header) - len(stats))\n   274→    sys.stdout.write(f\"{header}{' ' * padding}{stats}\\n\")\n   275→\n   276→    sys.stdout.flush()\n   277→    return 1\n   278→\n   279→\n   280→class ClaudeStallError(RuntimeError):\n   281→    \"\"\"Raised when Claude produces no output for CLAUDE_STALL_TIMEOUT seconds.\"\"\"\n   282→    pass\n   283→\n   284→\n   285→def _run_claude_once(\n   286→    prompt: str,\n   287→    model: str = \"sonnet\",\n   288→    log_path: Path | None = None,\n   289→) -> str:\n   290→    \"\"\"\n   291→    Run Claude Code in headless mode with live streaming display (single attempt).\n   292→\n   293→    Uses --output-format stream-json with --include-partial-messages to get\n   294→    real-time text deltas. Shows elapsed time and the last 5 lines of output.\n   295→    Saves full output to log_path if provided.\n   296→\n   297→    Raises ClaudeStallError if no output received for CLAUDE_STALL_TIMEOUT seconds.\n   298→    Raises RuntimeError on non-zero exit or overall timeout.\n   299→    \"\"\"\n   300→    cmd = [\n   301→        \"claude\", \"--print\", \"--dangerously-skip-permissions\",\n   302→        \"--verbose\",\n   303→        \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\",\n   304→        \"--include-partial-messages\",\n   305→    ]\n   306→\n   307→    model_ids = {\n   308→        \"opus\": \"claude-opus-4-6\",\n   309→        \"sonnet\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n   310→        \"haiku\": \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n   311→    }\n   312→    cmd.extend([\"--model\", model_ids.get(model, model_ids[\"sonnet\"])])\n   313→\n   314→    start = time.time()\n   315→    raw_lines: list[str] = []  # raw NDJSON lines for logging\n   316→    result_text = \"\"  # final result extracted from stream\n   317→    input_tokens = 0  # running count from message_start usage\n   318→    output_tokens = 0  # running count from message_delta usage\n   319→    last_activity = time.time()  # tracks last time model produced any output\n   320→    display_height = 0\n   321→    reader_done = threading.Event()\n   322→    lock = threading.Lock()\n   323→\n   324→    proc = subprocess.Popen(\n   325→        cmd,\n   326→        stdin=subprocess.PIPE,\n   327→        stdout=subprocess.PIPE,\n   328→        stderr=subprocess.PIPE,\n   329→        text=True,\n   330→        cwd=str(PROJECT_ROOT),\n   331→    )\n   332→\n   333→    # Send prompt and close stdin\n   334→    try:\n   335→        proc.stdin.write(prompt)\n   336→        proc.stdin.close()\n   337→    except BrokenPipeError:\n   338→        pass\n   339→\n   340→    # Read and parse stream-json stdout in background\n   341→    def reader():\n   342→        nonlocal result_text, input_tokens, output_tokens, last_activity\n   343→        try:\n   344→            for line in proc.stdout:\n   345→                raw_lines.append(line)\n   346→                stripped = line.strip()\n   347→                if not stripped:\n   348→                    continue\n   349→                try:\n   350→                    event = json.loads(stripped)\n   351→                except json.JSONDecodeError:\n   352→                    continue\n   353→\n   354→                etype = event.get(\"type\", \"\")\n   355→\n   356→                if etype == \"stream_event\":\n   357→                    nested = event.get(\"event\", {})\n   358→                    ntype = nested.get(\"type\", \"\")\n   359→                    # Any content_block_delta (thinking, text, tool JSON) = model is active\n   360→                    if ntype == \"content_block_delta\":\n   361→                        with lock:\n   362→                            last_activity = time.time()\n   363→                    # Track input tokens from message_start\n   364→                    elif ntype == \"message_start\":\n   365→                        usage = nested.get(\"message\", {}).get(\"usage\", {})\n   366→                        added = (usage.get(\"input_tokens\", 0)\n   367→                                 + usage.get(\"cache_creation_input_tokens\", 0)\n   368→                                 + usage.get(\"cache_read_input_tokens\", 0))\n   369→                        if added:\n   370→                            with lock:\n   371→                                input_tokens += added\n   372→                                last_activity = time.time()\n   373→                    # Track output tokens from message_delta\n   374→                    elif ntype == \"message_delta\":\n   375→                        usage = nested.get(\"usage\", {})\n   376→                        tok = usage.get(\"output_tokens\", 0)\n   377→                        if tok:\n   378→                            with lock:\n   379→                                output_tokens += tok\n   380→                                last_activity = time.time()\n   381→\n   382→                # Final result\n   383→                elif etype == \"result\":\n   384→                    result_text = event.get(\"result\", \"\")\n   385→        finally:\n   386→            reader_done.set()\n   387→\n   388→    thread = threading.Thread(target=reader, daemon=True)\n   389→    thread.start()\n   390→\n   391→    # Live display loop\n   392→    stall_timeout = CLAUDE_STALL_TIMEOUT_BY_MODEL.get(model, CLAUDE_STALL_TIMEOUT)\n   393→    stalled = False\n   394→    try:\n   395→        while not reader_done.is_set():\n   396→            elapsed = time.time() - start\n   397→\n   398→            # Overall timeout check\n   399→            if elapsed > CLAUDE_TIMEOUT:\n   400→                proc.kill()\n   401→                break\n   402→\n   403→            # Stall detection: no token traffic for stall_timeout seconds\n   404→            with lock:\n   405→                silence = time.time() - last_activity\n   406→            if silence > stall_timeout:\n   407→                stalled = True\n   408→                proc.kill()\n   409→                break\n   410→\n   411→            _clear_display(display_height)\n   412→            display_height = _render_display(model, elapsed, input_tokens, output_tokens)\n   413→\n   414→            reader_done.wait(timeout=1.0)\n   415→\n   416→        # Final display update\n   417→        elapsed = time.time() - start\n   418→        _clear_display(display_height)\n   419→        display_height = _render_display(model, elapsed, input_tokens, output_tokens)\n   420→\n   421→    except KeyboardInterrupt:\n   422→        proc.kill()\n   423→        _clear_display(display_height)\n   424→        print(f\"  Claude ({model}) interrupted by user\")\n   425→        raise\n   426→\n   427→    # Wait for process to finish\n   428→    try:\n   429→        proc.wait(timeout=30)\n   430→    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n   431→        proc.kill()\n   432→        proc.wait()\n   433→\n   434→    stderr_output = proc.stderr.read()\n   435→    elapsed = time.time() - start\n   436→\n   437→    # Use result from stream; fall back to joining raw output\n   438→    full_output = result_text or \"\".join(raw_lines)\n   439→\n   440→    # Save log (always, even on failure)\n   441→    if log_path:\n   442→        log_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n   443→        with open(log_path, \"w\") as f:\n   444→            f.write(f\"# Claude ({model}) — {time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}\\n\")\n   445→            f.write(f\"# Duration: {elapsed:.0f}s — Exit: {proc.returncode}\\n\")\n   446→            f.write(f\"# Prompt:\\n\")\n   447→            for pline in prompt.splitlines():\n   448→                f.write(f\"#   {pline}\\n\")\n   449→            f.write(f\"\\n{'=' * 60}\\n\\n\")\n   450→            f.write(result_text or \"\")\n   451→            if stderr_output:\n   452→                f.write(f\"\\n{'=' * 60}\\n# STDERR:\\n{stderr_output}\\n\")\n   453→            # Also save raw NDJSON stream for debugging\n   454→            f.write(f\"\\n{'=' * 60}\\n# RAW STREAM ({len(raw_lines)} events):\\n\")\n   455→            for rl in raw_lines:\n   456→                f.write(rl)\n   457→\n   458→    # Status line and error handling\n   459→    if stalled:\n   460→        msg = f\"Claude ({model}) stalled (no output for {stall_timeout}s) at {elapsed:.0f}s\"\n   461→        print(f\"\\n  {msg}\")\n   462→        raise ClaudeStallError(msg)\n   463→    elif proc.returncode == 0:\n   464→        print(f\"\\n  Claude ({model}) finished in {elapsed:.0f}s\")\n   465→    elif elapsed > CLAUDE_TIMEOUT:\n   466→        print(f\"\\n  Claude ({model}) timed out after {elapsed:.0f}s\")\n   467→        raise RuntimeError(f\"Claude ({model}) timed out after {elapsed:.0f}s\")\n   468→    else:\n   469→        msg = f\"Claude ({model}) failed (exit {proc.returncode}) in {elapsed:.0f}s\"\n   470→        print(f\"\\n  {msg}\")\n   471→        if stderr_output:\n   472→            print(f\"  stderr: {stderr_output[:500]}\")\n   473→        raise RuntimeError(f\"{msg}\\n{stderr_output[:1000]}\")\n   474→\n   475→    return result_text or full_output\n   476→\n   477→\n   478→def run_claude(\n   479→    prompt: str,\n   480→    model: str = \"sonnet\",\n   481→    log_path: Path | None = None,\n   482→) -> str:\n   483→    \"\"\"\n   484→    Run Claude Code with automatic retry on stalls.\n   485→\n   486→    Retries up to CLAUDE_MAX_RETRIES times when Claude stalls (no output for\n   487→    CLAUDE_STALL_TIMEOUT seconds). After exhausting retries, raises RuntimeError.\n   488→    Non-stall failures (exit code, overall timeout) are raised immediately.\n   489→    \"\"\"\n   490→    for attempt in range(1, CLAUDE_MAX_RETRIES + 1):\n   491→        try:\n   492→            return _run_claude_once(prompt, model=model, log_path=log_path)\n   493→        except ClaudeStallError:\n   494→            if attempt < CLAUDE_MAX_RETRIES:\n   495→                print(f\"  Retrying ({attempt}/{CLAUDE_MAX_RETRIES})...\")\n   496→            else:\n   497→                raise RuntimeError(\n   498→                    f\"Claude ({model}) stalled {CLAUDE_MAX_RETRIES} times — giving up\"\n   499→                )\n   500→    # unreachable, but satisfies type checker\n   501→    raise RuntimeError(\"unreachable\")\n   502→\n   503→\n   504→# --- Iteration phases ---\n   505→\n   506→def phase_evaluate(iteration: int, log_dir: Path) -> tuple[Path, float, list[dict]]:\n   507→    \"\"\"Run evaluation, write results, log accuracy. Returns (iter_dir, accuracy, results).\"\"\"\n   508→    print(f\"\\nEvaluating real input files...\")\n   509→    real_files = sorted(glob.glob(str(INPUT_DIR / \"*.real.txt\")))\n   510→    print(f\"  Found {len(real_files)} real files\")\n   511→    real_results = evaluate_files(real_files)\n   512→    real_accuracy = compute_accuracy(real_results)\n   513→    print(f\"\\n  Real accuracy: {real_accuracy:.1%} ({sum(1 for r in real_results if r['match'])}/{len(real_results)})\")\n   514→\n   515→    gen_results: list[dict] = []\n   516→    combined_accuracy = real_accuracy\n   517→\n   518→    # If real accuracy is high enough, test on generated data too\n   519→    if real_accuracy >= ACCURACY_THRESHOLD:\n   520→        print(f\"\\nGenerating {SYNTHETIC_COUNT} synthetic OCR files...\")\n   521→        generate_synthetic_data(iteration, log_dir=log_dir)\n   522→\n   523→        print(f\"\\nEvaluating generated files...\")\n   524→        gen_files = sorted(glob.glob(str(INPUT_DIR / f\"*.generated.{iteration}.txt\")))\n   525→        print(f\"  Found {len(gen_files)} generated files\")\n   526→        if gen_files:\n   527→            gen_results = evaluate_files(gen_files)\n   528→            gen_accuracy = compute_accuracy(gen_results)\n   529→            print(f\"\\n  Generated accuracy: {gen_accuracy:.1%}\")\n   530→            combined_accuracy = compute_accuracy(real_results + gen_results)\n   531→        else:\n   532→            print(\"  WARNING: No generated files found. Claude may have failed.\")\n   533→\n   534→    all_results = real_results + gen_results\n   535→    print(f\"\\n  Combined accuracy: {combined_accuracy:.1%}\")\n   536→\n   537→    # Log iteration accuracy\n   538→    with open(ITER_LOG, \"a\") as f:\n   539→        f.write(f\"{iteration} - {combined_accuracy:.1%}\\n\")\n   540→\n   541→    # Create iteration directory and write results\n   542→    commit_hash = get_commit_hash()\n   543→    iter_dir = DOCS_DIR / f\"{iteration}-{commit_hash}\"\n   544→    write_results(iter_dir, all_results)\n   545→    print(f\"  Results written to {iter_dir.relative_to(PROJECT_ROOT)}\")\n   546→\n   547→    return iter_dir, combined_accuracy, all_results\n   548→\n   549→\n   550→def generate_synthetic_data(iteration: int, log_dir: Path) -> None:\n   551→    \"\"\"Generate synthetic OCR data using Claude Code.\"\"\"\n   552→    real_files = glob.glob(str(INPUT_DIR / \"*.real.txt\"))\n   553→    existing_titles = [extract_expected_title(f) for f in real_files]\n   554→    titles_list = \", \".join(existing_titles)\n   555→\n   556→    prompt = f\"\"\"Generate {SYNTHETIC_COUNT} realistic fake OCR recipe text files.\n   557→\n   558→Each file should simulate real OCR output from a scanned cookbook page. Include typical\n   559→OCR artifacts: slightly misrecognized characters, broken line wraps, page numbers,\n   560→headers/footers, section labels.\n   561→\n   562→Save each file to: tools/title-loop/input/{{RECIPE_TITLE}}.generated.{iteration}.txt\n   563→\n   564→The recipe title in the filename must EXACTLY match the main title as it appears in the\n   565→generated text content (case-insensitive matching is fine, but the words must match).\n   566→\n   567→Requirements:\n   568→- Mix of English and Polish recipes (roughly 60/40)\n   569→- Variety: soups, mains, desserts, salads, appetizers, breads, drinks, preserves\n   570→- Include multi-word titles (2-5 words), some single-word titles\n   571→- Include OCR noise: garbled short lines at top/bottom, stray numbers, broken words\n   572→- Some files should have the title after noise/headers (not first line)\n   573→- Vary title position: top, after page number, after section header, mid-page\n   574→- Some should have section headers like INGREDIENTS, SKŁADNIKI before or near the title\n   575→- Generate DIFFERENT recipes than these existing ones: {titles_list}\n   576→- Each file should be 15-40 lines long\n   577→\n   578→Generate all {SYNTHETIC_COUNT} files. Work through them systematically.\"\"\"\n   579→\n   580→    run_claude(prompt, model=\"haiku\", log_path=log_dir / \"generate.log\")\n   581→\n   582→\n   583→def phase_analyze(iter_dir: Path, results: list[dict]) -> None:\n   584→    \"\"\"Analyze extraction failures with Claude (Sonnet).\"\"\"\n   585→    log_dir = iter_dir / \"logs\"\n   586→    failures = [r for r in results if not r[\"match\"]]\n   587→    if not failures:\n   588→        (iter_dir / \"feedback.md\").write_text(\"No failures to analyze — all extractions matched.\\n\")\n   589→        return\n   590→\n   591→    failure_details = \"\\n\".join(\n   592→        f\"- File: {r['file']}\\n  Expected: '{r['expected']}'\\n  Got: '{r['extracted']}'\"\n   593→        for r in failures\n   594→    )\n   595→\n   596→    prompt = f\"\"\"Analyze the title extraction failures below. Read each failing input file\n   597→and the current implementation at lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts.\n   598→\n   599→Write your analysis to {iter_dir.relative_to(PROJECT_ROOT)}/feedback.md explaining:\n   600→1. What patterns the algorithm fails on\n   601→2. Why each specific failure occurred\n   602→3. Common themes across failures\n   603→\n   604→Do NOT modify any code files. Only write the feedback.md file.\n   605→\n   606→Failures:\n   607→{failure_details}\n   608→\n   609→Results file: {iter_dir.relative_to(PROJECT_ROOT)}/results.txt\"\"\"\n   610→\n   611→    run_claude(prompt, model=\"sonnet\", log_path=log_dir / \"analyze.log\")\n   612→\n   613→\n   614→def phase_plan(iter_dir: Path, iteration: int) -> None:\n   615→    \"\"\"Plan algorithm improvements with Claude (Opus).\"\"\"\n   616→    log_dir = iter_dir / \"logs\"\n   617→    prompt = f\"\"\"Read the feedback at {iter_dir.relative_to(PROJECT_ROOT)}/feedback.md\n   618→and the current title extraction implementation at lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts.\n   619→Also read previous iteration docs in tools/title-loop/docs/ to understand what has been tried.\n   620→\n   621→Your job: propose changes that fix every failure. Think creatively and ambitiously.\n   622→\n   623→Hard constraints:\n   624→- Must run on a mobile device (React Native / Expo)\n   625→- Total title extraction must complete under 10 seconds\n   626→- Changes land in lib/text-classifier/ and related files\n   627→\n   628→Everything else is open for debate. The current approach (MiniLM embeddings + heuristic scoring)\n   629→is one option, but you are free to propose alternatives if they'd work better:\n   630→- Different embedding model or similarity strategy\n   631→- Replacing embeddings entirely with a rule-based or hybrid approach\n   632→- Restructuring the pipeline (e.g., two-pass, re-ranking, candidate merging)\n   633→- Changing how candidates are generated, filtered, or deduplicated\n   634→- Any other approach that solves the failures within the hard constraints\n   635→\n   636→Don't be incremental for the sake of it — if the feedback reveals a fundamental design flaw,\n   637→propose a fundamental fix. But also don't change things that already work well.\n   638→\n   639→Before writing any files, briefly outline your key proposed changes (2-3 sentences per failure)\n   640→so you can think through the approach first.\n   641→\n   642→Then write a detailed improvement plan to {iter_dir.relative_to(PROJECT_ROOT)}/improvement-plan.md\n   643→that includes:\n   644→1. Root cause analysis for each failure pattern\n   645→2. Specific code changes with before/after examples\n   646→3. New or modified heuristics, scoring adjustments, or pipeline changes\n   647→4. Expected impact on accuracy\n   648→\n   649→Do NOT modify any code files. Only write the improvement-plan.md file.\"\"\"\n   650→\n   651→    run_claude(prompt, model=\"opus\", log_path=log_dir / \"plan.log\")\n   652→\n   653→\n   654→def phase_execute(iter_dir: Path) -> None:\n   655→    \"\"\"Execute improvements with Claude (Sonnet), verify, and commit.\"\"\"\n   656→    log_dir = iter_dir / \"logs\"\n   657→    prompt = f\"\"\"Execute the improvement plan at {iter_dir.relative_to(PROJECT_ROOT)}/improvement-plan.md.\n   658→\n   659→Modify lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts and any related files as needed.\n   660→Make sure:\n   661→1. All existing tests still pass\n   662→2. The CLI at tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts still works\n   663→3. The code is clean and follows the project conventions in AGENTS.md\n   664→4. No unnecessary changes outside the title extraction logic\n   665→\n   666→CRITICAL CONSTRAINT: Do NOT modify the substring deduplication logic in title-extractor.ts.\n   667→The block starting with \"// Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter\"\n   668→must remain exactly as-is. It keeps the SHORTER candidate. Do not invert this to keep the longer.\n   669→This has been incorrectly changed 5 times and breaks tests every time.\n   670→\n   671→After making changes, run: npx vitest run --globals lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts\n   672→Fix any test failures before finishing.\"\"\"\n   673→\n   674→    run_claude(prompt, model=\"sonnet\", log_path=log_dir / \"execute.log\")\n   675→\n   676→    # Verify tests and CLI\n   677→    print(f\"\\nVerifying tests and CLI...\")\n   678→    tests_ok = run_tests()\n   679→    cli_ok = verify_cli()\n   680→\n   681→    if not tests_ok or not cli_ok:\n   682→        print(\"  WARNING: Verification failed. Attempting to fix...\")\n   683→        fix_prompt = \"\"\"The title extraction tests or CLI are failing after recent changes.\n   684→Please fix any issues in lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts.\n   685→Run: npx vitest run lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts\n   686→And verify: npx tsx tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts tools/title-loop/input/*.real.txt\n   687→Make sure both pass before finishing.\"\"\"\n   688→        run_claude(fix_prompt, model=\"sonnet\", log_path=log_dir / \"fix.log\")\n   689→\n   690→        if not run_tests() or not verify_cli():\n   691→            raise RuntimeError(\"Tests or CLI still failing after fix attempt\")\n   692→\n   693→\n   694→def run_tests() -> bool:\n   695→    \"\"\"Run the title extraction tests.\"\"\"\n   696→    print(\"  Running tests...\")\n   697→    result = subprocess.run(\n   698→        [\"npx\", \"vitest\", \"run\", \"--globals\", \"lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts\"],\n   699→        capture_output=True,\n   700→        text=True,\n   701→        timeout=120,\n   702→        cwd=str(PROJECT_ROOT),\n   703→    )\n   704→    if result.returncode != 0:\n   705→        print(f\"  Tests FAILED: {result.stdout[-500:]}\")\n   706→        return False\n   707→    print(\"  Tests passed.\")\n   708→    return True\n   709→\n   710→\n   711→def verify_cli() -> bool:\n   712→    \"\"\"Verify the CLI script runs without errors on a sample file.\"\"\"\n   713→    real_files = glob.glob(str(INPUT_DIR / \"*.real.txt\"))\n   714→    if not real_files:\n   715→        print(\"  No real files to test CLI with\")\n   716→        return False\n   717→\n   718→    sample = real_files[0]\n   719→    print(f\"  Verifying CLI on: {Path(sample).name}\")\n   720→    result = subprocess.run(\n   721→        [\"npx\", \"tsx\", str(EXTRACT_SCRIPT), sample],\n   722→        capture_output=True,\n   723→        text=True,\n   724→        timeout=EXTRACT_TIMEOUT,\n   725→        cwd=str(PROJECT_ROOT),\n   726→    )\n   727→    if result.returncode != 0:\n   728→        print(f\"  CLI verification FAILED: {result.stderr[:300]}\")\n   729→        return False\n   730→    print(f\"  CLI output: '{result.stdout.strip()}'\")\n   731→    return True\n   732→\n   733→\n   734→# --- Main loop ---\n   735→\n   736→def main() -> None:\n   737→    \"\"\"Main self-improving loop with full mid-iteration resumability.\"\"\"\n   738→    DOCS_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n   739→\n   740→    last_logged = get_last_logged_iteration()\n   741→    if last_logged > 0:\n   742→        last_phase = determine_resume_phase(last_logged)\n   743→        if last_phase == \"done\":\n   744→            accuracy = get_logged_accuracy(last_logged)\n   745→            if accuracy is not None and accuracy >= ACCURACY_THRESHOLD:\n   746→                print(f\"Iteration {last_logged} already reached target accuracy ({accuracy:.1%}). Nothing to do.\")\n   747→                return\n   748→            start_iteration = last_logged + 1\n   749→        else:\n   750→            start_iteration = last_logged\n   751→    else:\n   752→        start_iteration = 1\n   753→\n   754→    print(\"=\" * 60)\n   755→    print(\"SELF-IMPROVING TITLE EXTRACTION LOOP\")\n   756→    print(f\"Max iterations: {MAX_ITERATIONS}\")\n   757→    print(f\"Accuracy threshold: {ACCURACY_THRESHOLD:.0%}\")\n   758→    print(f\"Input dir: {INPUT_DIR}\")\n   759→    if start_iteration > 1:\n   760→        phase = determine_resume_phase(start_iteration)\n   761→        print(f\"Resuming: iteration {start_iteration}, phase '{phase}'\")\n   762→    print(\"=\" * 60)\n   763→    print()\n   764→\n   765→    # Verify CLI works before starting\n   766→    print(\"Pre-flight: verifying CLI...\")\n   767→    if not verify_cli():\n   768→        print(\"FATAL: CLI verification failed. Fix before running the loop.\")\n   769→        sys.exit(1)\n   770→    print()\n   771→\n   772→    for iteration in range(start_iteration, MAX_ITERATIONS + 1):\n   773→        phase = determine_resume_phase(iteration)\n   774→\n   775→        if phase == \"done\":\n   776→            print(f\"Iteration {iteration} already completed. Skipping.\")\n   777→            continue\n   778→\n   779→        print(\"=\" * 60)\n   780→        print(f\"ITERATION {iteration}\" + (f\"  (resuming from '{phase}')\" if phase != \"evaluate\" else \"\"))\n   781→        print(\"=\" * 60)\n   782→\n   783→        iter_dir = find_iter_dir(iteration)\n   784→        all_results: list[dict] | None = None\n   785→\n   786→        # Ensure logs dir exists for this iteration\n   787→        if iter_dir:\n   788→            (iter_dir / \"logs\").mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n   789→\n   790→        # --- EVALUATE ---\n   791→        if phase == \"evaluate\":\n   792→            # Create provisional log dir (iter_dir doesn't exist yet)\n   793→            commit_hash = get_commit_hash()\n   794→            provisional_log_dir = DOCS_DIR / f\"{iteration}-{commit_hash}\" / \"logs\"\n   795→            provisional_log_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n   796→\n   797→            try:\n   798→                iter_dir, combined_accuracy, all_results = phase_evaluate(iteration, log_dir=provisional_log_dir)\n   799→            except RuntimeError as e:\n   800→                print(f\"  FATAL: {e}. Stopping.\")\n   801→                break\n   802→\n   803→            if combined_accuracy >= ACCURACY_THRESHOLD:\n   804→                print(f\"\\n{'=' * 60}\")\n   805→                print(f\"TARGET ACCURACY REACHED: {combined_accuracy:.1%}\")\n   806→                print(f\"Stopping after iteration {iteration}\")\n   807→                print(f\"{'=' * 60}\")\n   808→                break\n   809→\n   810→        assert iter_dir is not None, f\"No iteration directory found for iteration {iteration}\"\n   811→\n   812→        # --- ANALYZE ---\n   813→        if phase in (\"evaluate\", \"analyze\"):\n   814→            print(f\"\\nAnalyzing failures with Claude (Sonnet)...\")\n   815→            if all_results is None:\n   816→                all_results = load_results_from_file(iter_dir)\n   817→            try:\n   818→                phase_analyze(iter_dir, all_results)\n   819→            except RuntimeError as e:\n   820→                print(f\"  FATAL: {e}. Stopping.\")\n   821→                break\n   822→\n   823→        # --- PLAN ---\n   824→        if phase in (\"evaluate\", \"analyze\", \"plan\"):\n   825→            print(f\"\\nPlanning improvements with Claude (Opus)...\")\n   826→            try:\n   827→                phase_plan(iter_dir, iteration)\n   828→            except RuntimeError as e:\n   829→                print(f\"  FATAL: {e}. Stopping.\")\n   830→                break\n   831→\n   832→        # --- EXECUTE + VERIFY + COMMIT ---\n   833→        print(f\"\\nExecuting improvements with Claude (Sonnet)...\")\n   834→        try:\n   835→            phase_execute(iter_dir)\n   836→        except RuntimeError as e:\n   837→            print(f\"  FATAL: {e}. Stopping.\")\n   838→            break\n   839→\n   840→        # Commit changes\n   841→        print(f\"\\nCommitting changes...\")\n   842→        try:\n   843→            commit_hash = git_commit_all(f\"title-extraction: iteration {iteration}\")\n   844→            print(f\"  Committed: {commit_hash}\")\n   845→        except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e:\n   846→            # git commit exits 1 both for \"nothing to commit\" and real failures.\n   847→            # Check git status to distinguish.\n   848→            status = subprocess.run(\n   849→                [\"git\", \"status\", \"--porcelain\"],\n   850→                capture_output=True, text=True, cwd=str(PROJECT_ROOT),\n   851→            )\n   852→            if not status.stdout.strip():\n   853→                print(\"  WARNING: Nothing to commit (no changes made)\")\n   854→                commit_hash = get_commit_hash()\n   855→            else:\n   856→                print(f\"  FATAL: git commit failed: {e}. Stopping.\")\n   857→                break\n   858→\n   859→        # Mark iteration as committed so resume skips it\n   860→        (iter_dir / \"committed\").write_text(f\"{commit_hash}\\n\")\n   861→\n   862→        # Prepare next iteration directory\n   863→        next_dir = DOCS_DIR / f\"{iteration + 1}-{commit_hash}\"\n   864→        next_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n   865→\n   866→        print(f\"\\n  Next iteration dir: {next_dir.relative_to(PROJECT_ROOT)}\")\n   867→        print()\n   868→\n   869→    else:\n   870→        print(f\"\\n{'=' * 60}\")\n   871→        print(f\"MAX ITERATIONS ({MAX_ITERATIONS}) REACHED\")\n   872→        print(f\"Final accuracy may not have met threshold.\")\n   873→        print(f\"{'=' * 60}\")\n   874→\n   875→    # Print summary\n   876→    print(f\"\\nIteration log:\")\n   877→    if ITER_LOG.exists():\n   878→        print(ITER_LOG.read_text())\n   879→\n   880→\n   881→if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n   882→    main()\n   883→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014SMcitGhR7RLPNfFUpgyat","session_id":"dda4a6e7-7d44-4b1e-8d84-edc63f9f063b","uuid":"502130ec-09af-42d3-b6d3-97670e582df5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QwwNakJ9opoG8LxDs8K1jY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Iteration 5 Failure Analysis\n     2→\n     3→## Failures\n     4→\n     5→### 1. `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander` → `''`\n     6→\n     7→**What happened:** Nothing was returned.\n     8→\n     9→**Why:** The title is split across two lines:\n    10→```\n    11→Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce    ← line 1\n    12→& Coriander                                    ← line 2\n    13→```\n    14→\n    15→The 2-line join (`Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander`, 54 chars) passes hard filters. But the deduplication step removes it: the shorter single line `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce` is a substring of the join, so the join is discarded in favor of the partial line. After dedup only the partial survives — but it may not pass the threshold (no ALL_CAPS bonus, no structural bonus, mixed-case title).\n    16→\n    17→The deeper issue is that `& Coriander` is also a candidate (passes hard filters), and the dedup logic's \"shorter wins\" rule is designed to prevent ingredient run-ons but here it actively destroys the correct multi-line title join.\n    18→\n    19→If the partial single line does score above threshold, the output would be `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce` — not an exact match to expected — but the run reports `''`, suggesting either the partial also fails threshold, or something else causes all candidates to be filtered.\n    20→\n    21→**Root cause:** Split mixed-case title + deduplication's \"shorter wins\" rule destroys the 2-line join that is the correct answer.\n    22→\n    23→---\n    24→\n    25→### 2. `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS` → `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS`\n    26→\n    27→**What happened:** Only the first title was returned; the second was dropped.\n    28→\n    29→**Why:** Both titles appear as clean standalone ALL_CAPS lines well within the document (lines 16 and 29 of 43). The algorithm should recognize both as a multi-recipe page.\n    30→\n    31→Tracing through:\n    32→- `baseHeading` = `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS` (first structural heading, passes `isStructuralHeading` — all three sig words ≥ 4 letters).\n    33→- `firstStructuralHeading` = `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS` (no continuation extension found — `FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS` doesn't start with `\"finnish milk flatbreads \"`).\n    34→- `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS` receives `allCapsBonus (0.08) + structuralBonus (0.10) = 0.18` in total on top of its raw embedding score.\n    35→\n    36→The structural bonus inflates `bestBaseScore`, which raises the threshold via `bestBaseScore × 0.7`. `FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS` has only `allCapsBonus (0.08)` and receives no position boost (it appears at ~65% of the document, past the 50% cutoff). Its total score falls below the inflated threshold.\n    37→\n    38→The multi-title guard (`allCapsSelected.length >= 2 → keep both`) never fires because `FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS` is already filtered out before that point.\n    39→\n    40→**Root cause:** Structural heading bonus on the first title inflates `bestBaseScore`, raising the threshold so high that the second title — with identical ALL_CAPS quality but no structural bonus — fails to pass it.\n    41→\n    42→---\n    43→\n    44→### 3. `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)` → `FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)`\n    45→\n    46→**What happened:** A completely wrong, garbled OCR artifact was returned instead of the real title.\n    47→\n    48→**Why:** The page contains an earlier OCR corruption near line 29:\n    49→```\n    50→FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\n    51→```\n    52→This is a truncated rendering of `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS` with a garbled variation number. Despite being a junk artifact, it passes `isStructuralHeading`:\n    53→- All letters uppercase ✓\n    54→- sig words: `FRON`(4), `WHEAT`(5), `BUNS`(4), `(VARIATION`(9) — all ≥ 4 letters ✓\n    55→\n    56→So `baseHeading = \"FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\"` and it receives the full `structuralBonus (0.10) + allCapsBonus (0.08) = 0.18`.\n    57→\n    58→The correct title appears later (lines 54–55):\n    59→```\n    60→SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\n    61→/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\n    62→```\n    63→\n    64→The continuation extension logic was designed for exactly this pattern, but it only fires when `baseHeading` IS the correct title's first line — checking whether any candidate starts with `baseHeading.text + \" \"` followed by a continuation char. Since `baseHeading` is the wrong garbled line, the continuation logic never triggers for the real title.\n    65→\n    66→The 2-line join `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)` passes hard filters and would be the correct answer. But:\n    67→1. The garbled `FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)` inflates `bestBaseScore` with its structural bonus, raising the threshold.\n    68→2. The deduplication removes the join in favor of the shorter `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK` (which is a substring of the join).\n    69→3. `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK` (no structural bonus, no position boost at 70% document depth) likely falls just below the inflated threshold.\n    70→\n    71→Result: only the garbled candidate survives.\n    72→\n    73→**Root cause:** A garbled ALL_CAPS OCR fragment passes `isStructuralHeading` and hijacks the structural heading role. This awards `firstStructuralHeading` to the wrong candidate, disables the continuation extension for the real title, and inflates the threshold so the real title is excluded.\n    74→\n    75→---\n    76→\n    77→## Common Themes\n    78→\n    79→### Theme 1: Structural bonus inflates threshold, excluding correct titles (cases 2 and 3)\n    80→\n    81→The comment at line 328 notes that `baseScore` (without position factor) is used for the threshold so that position boost doesn't inflate the bar. But `baseScore` still includes `allCapsBonus` and `structuralBonus`. The structural bonus (+0.10) is large enough that `bestBaseScore × 0.7` rises above what a correct ALL_CAPS title without the structural bonus can achieve. The fix attempted for position leakage was not applied to bonus leakage.\n    82→\n    83→### Theme 2: \"Shorter wins\" deduplication destroys multi-line title joins (cases 1 and 3)\n    84→\n    85→The dedup rule removes a candidate `a` if any shorter candidate `b` is a substring of it. This correctly prevents ingredient run-ons, but it also destroys 2-line title joins: the first half of the title (a shorter candidate) causes the complete join to be eliminated. The join is the only correct answer on split-title pages.\n    86→\n    87→### Theme 3: `isStructuralHeading` accepts garbled OCR fragments (case 3)\n    88→\n    89→The check requires ALL_CAPS, ≥2 sig words, and each sig word ≥4 uppercase letters. This is satisfied by truncated OCR artifacts like `FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)`. There is no check that the candidate is semantically plausible as a recipe title before awarding it the structural bonus and the `firstStructuralHeading` role.\n    90→\n    91→### Theme 4: Mixed-case titles receive no bonuses and may fall below the floor threshold (case 1)\n    92→\n    93→Titles like `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander` get no `allCapsBonus` and no `structuralBonus`. With a floor threshold of `0.08`, a plausible recipe title that scores moderately in embeddings may still be filtered out — especially if any ALL_CAPS candidate (even a bad one) drives up `bestBaseScore`.\n    94→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Mec9R64nuL6YcE5gmCxs41","session_id":"dda4a6e7-7d44-4b1e-8d84-edc63f9f063b","uuid":"d243ddd0-64d2-4fe4-8a0c-3b532aa287c1"}
