{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014SMcitGhR7RLPNfFUpgyat","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me compile the comprehensive summary:\n\n## Summary: Title Extraction System Test Cases, Ground Truth, and Evaluation\n\n### Overview\nThe title extraction system is a self-improving loop that iteratively evaluates and improves recipe title extraction from OCR text. The system uses semantic embeddings (MiniLM model) combined with heuristic scoring to extract titles from noisy OCR input across English and Polish recipes.\n\n### Ground Truth Test Cases (9 Total)\n\n**Real Input Files** (9 files in `/tools/title-loop/input/`):\n\n1. **ARAYES SHRAK.real.txt** — Arabic/Palestinian recipe with title split across two lines (\"ARAYES\" / \"SHRAK\")\n2. **Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander.real.txt** — English title split with continuation character (\"&\")\n3. **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM.real.txt** — Polish bread recipe with intra-recipe section headers\n4. **FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS.real.txt** — Multi-recipe page with two titles joined by \"+\"\n5. **Faszerowana papryka.real.txt** — Polish title with ALL_CAPS subtitle/romanization\n6. **MIXED SEED CRISPBREAD.real.txt** — Simple single title\n7. **OVERNIGHT STRAIGHT PIZZA DOUGH.real.txt** — Simple single title\n8. **SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D).real.txt** — Title with OCR character corruption (:→/) and garbled prior content\n9. **Plus 2 new Polish recipes** (added March 14-15) for testing edge cases\n\n### Evaluation Methodology\n\n**The title-loop.py orchestrates a 5-phase self-improving cycle:**\n\n1. **Phase: Evaluate** — Runs extraction against real input files using `/tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts` CLI. Compares `extractTitleWithEmbeddings()` output against expected title (parsed from filename, e.g., `\"ARAYES SHRAK.real.txt\"` → expected: `\"ARAYES SHRAK\"`). Generates synthetic test data (100 files per iteration) if real accuracy ≥ 95%.\n\n2. **Phase: Analyze** — Claude (Sonnet) reads failure cases and writes `/tools/title-loop/docs/{iter}-{hash}/feedback.md` explaining why each failure occurred.\n\n3. **Phase: Plan** — Claude (Opus) reads feedback and current code, proposes improvements to `/tools/title-loop/docs/{iter}-{hash}/improvement-plan.md`.\n\n4. **Phase: Execute** — Claude (Sonnet) implements changes to `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`, runs `npx vitest run lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts`, verifies CLI works.\n\n5. **Phase: Commit** — Git commits all changes and records accuracy in `tools/title-loop/docs/iter.txt`.\n\n**Matching Logic:**\n- Expected: parsed from filename, may contain multiple titles separated by \"+\" (e.g., `\"FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS\"`)\n- Extracted: returned by `extractTitleWithEmbeddings()`, joined with \" + \"\n- Match: extracted title must contain all expected parts (case-insensitive, with filesystem substitution `\":\" → \"/\"`), supporting partial multi-title matches\n\n**Accuracy Threshold:** 95% (stop loop when reached across real + synthetic test sets)\n\n### Iteration Progress\n\n```\nIteration 1: 16.7% (1/6 real tests passing)\nIteration 2: 16.7% (stalled)\nIteration 3: 33.3% (2/6)\nIteration 4: 50.0% (3/6)\nIteration 5: 50.0% (stalled)\nIteration 6: 66.7% (4/7) — reached best accuracy\nIteration 7: 50.0% (4/8) — regression after Polish data added\n```\n\n### Current Test Suite (Unit Tests)\n\nLocated at `/lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts` (214 lines, 27 test cases):\n\n**Test groups:**\n- **extractTitle (heuristic fallback, 5 tests):** Sync/non-embedding baseline covering empty text, first valid line, filtering long/short/ingredient/all-caps/numbered lines\n- **extractTitleWithEmbeddings (22 tests):** Semantic extraction with mock embeddings covering:\n  - Empty/whitespace handling\n  - Title vs. section header prioritization (Polish/English)\n  - ALL_CAPS title preservation\n  - Multi-line title joining (2-line, 3-line cases)\n  - Preventing over-greedy joining with headers\n  - Multiple titles on same page (returns \"+ \" joined)\n  - Garbled burst detection (skip 3+ short garbled lines, find title after)\n  - Deep-text multiple titles\n  - Single-recipe recovery\n  - ALL_CAPS structural heading edge cases (ARAYES SHRAK, SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK variants)\n\n**Mock embedding strategy:** Synthetic embed function that returns 3D vectors: dimension 0 = title similarity, dimension 1 = header similarity, dimension 2 = noise similarity.\n\n### Current Failures (Iteration 7, 4/8 passing = 50%)\n\n1. **Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander** — Continuation join (\"&\") below embedding threshold; suffix fragment (\"& Coriander\") survives and kills the join via dedup \"shorter wins\" rule.\n\n2. **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** — Intra-recipe ALL_CAPS section header (\"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\") qualifies as structural heading, multi-title guard detects 2+ ALL_CAPS and returns both joined.\n\n3. **Faszerowana papryka** — Polish title (mixed-case, position 0) outranked by ALL_CAPS Korean romanization (position 1) due to +0.18 bonus (ALL_CAPS +0.08 + structural +0.10) overriding positional factor.\n\n4. **SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)** — Two issues: (A) OCR corruption (`:` → `/`) makes exact string impossible to match; (B) 2-line join likely excluded from top-25 pre-filter, leaving only partial title.\n\n### Key Algorithm Components\n\n**Hard filters** (lines must pass all): 3–80 chars, non-ingredient, non-numbered, non-metadata, non-garbled\n**Garbled detection:** Vowel ratio <15% or >85%, orphaned short words, lowercase start, sentence fragments, multi-word with unknown lowercase words\n**Structural heading detection:** ALL_CAPS, ≥2 significant words (≥4 letters each), significant punctuation filtered\n**Scoring:** rawScore (title_sim − max(header_sim, noise_sim)) + bonuses (position factor, ALL_CAPS +0.08, structural +0.10)\n**Threshold:** max(0.08, bestThresholdScore × 0.7)\n**Multi-line joining:** Supports 2-line and 3-line joins; continuation protection filters single-line prefixes of surviving 2-line joins starting with /&+:(\n**Deduplication:** If one candidate is a substring of another, keep the shorter (with careful protection for continuation joins via pre-filters)\n**Multi-title guard:** If ≥2 ALL_CAPS survivors → return all; if 1 ALL_CAPS → collapse to highest-scoring; if 0 ALL_CAPS → keep all\n\n### Recent Changes (Iteration 6 & 7 attempts)\n\nIteration 6 added continuation join protection to prevent prefix singles from killing the complete join. This fixed cases like ARAYES SHRAK but introduced regression in Iteration 7 with Polish data (accurate detection of new edge case: intra-recipe headers).\n\n### Absolute File Paths\n\n- **Loop orchestrator:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/title-loop.py`\n- **CLI:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts`\n- **Core implementation:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n- **Unit tests:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts`\n- **Input files:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/` (9 .real.txt files)\n- **Iteration docs:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/{1-7}-{hash}/` (results.txt, feedback.md, improvement-plan.md, committed)\n- **Log:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/iter.txt` (accuracy history)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7b3a6de9ecda5e21 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 87591\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 47655</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dda4a6e7-7d44-4b1e-8d84-edc63f9f063b","uuid":"bfea5834-24fc-4535-b874-aabce7e9536b","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the test files and input data for the title extraction system:\n1. Find and read test files related to title extraction in /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/ (look for files matching *title-extract* or *title_extract* in test directories)\n2. Read the input files in /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/ to understand what real recipe texts look like\n3. Read the iter.txt file at /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/iter.txt\n4. Read /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/title-loop.py to understand how the evaluation loop works\n\nSummarize: what test cases exist, what's in the ground truth, and how the evaluation works.","agentId":"a7b3a6de9ecda5e21","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me compile the comprehensive summary:\n\n## Summary: Title Extraction System Test Cases, Ground Truth, and Evaluation\n\n### Overview\nThe title extraction system is a self-improving loop that iteratively evaluates and improves recipe title extraction from OCR text. The system uses semantic embeddings (MiniLM model) combined with heuristic scoring to extract titles from noisy OCR input across English and Polish recipes.\n\n### Ground Truth Test Cases (9 Total)\n\n**Real Input Files** (9 files in `/tools/title-loop/input/`):\n\n1. **ARAYES SHRAK.real.txt** — Arabic/Palestinian recipe with title split across two lines (\"ARAYES\" / \"SHRAK\")\n2. **Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander.real.txt** — English title split with continuation character (\"&\")\n3. **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM.real.txt** — Polish bread recipe with intra-recipe section headers\n4. **FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS.real.txt** — Multi-recipe page with two titles joined by \"+\"\n5. **Faszerowana papryka.real.txt** — Polish title with ALL_CAPS subtitle/romanization\n6. **MIXED SEED CRISPBREAD.real.txt** — Simple single title\n7. **OVERNIGHT STRAIGHT PIZZA DOUGH.real.txt** — Simple single title\n8. **SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D).real.txt** — Title with OCR character corruption (:→/) and garbled prior content\n9. **Plus 2 new Polish recipes** (added March 14-15) for testing edge cases\n\n### Evaluation Methodology\n\n**The title-loop.py orchestrates a 5-phase self-improving cycle:**\n\n1. **Phase: Evaluate** — Runs extraction against real input files using `/tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts` CLI. Compares `extractTitleWithEmbeddings()` output against expected title (parsed from filename, e.g., `\"ARAYES SHRAK.real.txt\"` → expected: `\"ARAYES SHRAK\"`). Generates synthetic test data (100 files per iteration) if real accuracy ≥ 95%.\n\n2. **Phase: Analyze** — Claude (Sonnet) reads failure cases and writes `/tools/title-loop/docs/{iter}-{hash}/feedback.md` explaining why each failure occurred.\n\n3. **Phase: Plan** — Claude (Opus) reads feedback and current code, proposes improvements to `/tools/title-loop/docs/{iter}-{hash}/improvement-plan.md`.\n\n4. **Phase: Execute** — Claude (Sonnet) implements changes to `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`, runs `npx vitest run lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts`, verifies CLI works.\n\n5. **Phase: Commit** — Git commits all changes and records accuracy in `tools/title-loop/docs/iter.txt`.\n\n**Matching Logic:**\n- Expected: parsed from filename, may contain multiple titles separated by \"+\" (e.g., `\"FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS\"`)\n- Extracted: returned by `extractTitleWithEmbeddings()`, joined with \" + \"\n- Match: extracted title must contain all expected parts (case-insensitive, with filesystem substitution `\":\" → \"/\"`), supporting partial multi-title matches\n\n**Accuracy Threshold:** 95% (stop loop when reached across real + synthetic test sets)\n\n### Iteration Progress\n\n```\nIteration 1: 16.7% (1/6 real tests passing)\nIteration 2: 16.7% (stalled)\nIteration 3: 33.3% (2/6)\nIteration 4: 50.0% (3/6)\nIteration 5: 50.0% (stalled)\nIteration 6: 66.7% (4/7) — reached best accuracy\nIteration 7: 50.0% (4/8) — regression after Polish data added\n```\n\n### Current Test Suite (Unit Tests)\n\nLocated at `/lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts` (214 lines, 27 test cases):\n\n**Test groups:**\n- **extractTitle (heuristic fallback, 5 tests):** Sync/non-embedding baseline covering empty text, first valid line, filtering long/short/ingredient/all-caps/numbered lines\n- **extractTitleWithEmbeddings (22 tests):** Semantic extraction with mock embeddings covering:\n  - Empty/whitespace handling\n  - Title vs. section header prioritization (Polish/English)\n  - ALL_CAPS title preservation\n  - Multi-line title joining (2-line, 3-line cases)\n  - Preventing over-greedy joining with headers\n  - Multiple titles on same page (returns \"+ \" joined)\n  - Garbled burst detection (skip 3+ short garbled lines, find title after)\n  - Deep-text multiple titles\n  - Single-recipe recovery\n  - ALL_CAPS structural heading edge cases (ARAYES SHRAK, SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK variants)\n\n**Mock embedding strategy:** Synthetic embed function that returns 3D vectors: dimension 0 = title similarity, dimension 1 = header similarity, dimension 2 = noise similarity.\n\n### Current Failures (Iteration 7, 4/8 passing = 50%)\n\n1. **Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander** — Continuation join (\"&\") below embedding threshold; suffix fragment (\"& Coriander\") survives and kills the join via dedup \"shorter wins\" rule.\n\n2. **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** — Intra-recipe ALL_CAPS section header (\"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\") qualifies as structural heading, multi-title guard detects 2+ ALL_CAPS and returns both joined.\n\n3. **Faszerowana papryka** — Polish title (mixed-case, position 0) outranked by ALL_CAPS Korean romanization (position 1) due to +0.18 bonus (ALL_CAPS +0.08 + structural +0.10) overriding positional factor.\n\n4. **SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)** — Two issues: (A) OCR corruption (`:` → `/`) makes exact string impossible to match; (B) 2-line join likely excluded from top-25 pre-filter, leaving only partial title.\n\n### Key Algorithm Components\n\n**Hard filters** (lines must pass all): 3–80 chars, non-ingredient, non-numbered, non-metadata, non-garbled\n**Garbled detection:** Vowel ratio <15% or >85%, orphaned short words, lowercase start, sentence fragments, multi-word with unknown lowercase words\n**Structural heading detection:** ALL_CAPS, ≥2 significant words (≥4 letters each), significant punctuation filtered\n**Scoring:** rawScore (title_sim − max(header_sim, noise_sim)) + bonuses (position factor, ALL_CAPS +0.08, structural +0.10)\n**Threshold:** max(0.08, bestThresholdScore × 0.7)\n**Multi-line joining:** Supports 2-line and 3-line joins; continuation protection filters single-line prefixes of surviving 2-line joins starting with /&+:(\n**Deduplication:** If one candidate is a substring of another, keep the shorter (with careful protection for continuation joins via pre-filters)\n**Multi-title guard:** If ≥2 ALL_CAPS survivors → return all; if 1 ALL_CAPS → collapse to highest-scoring; if 0 ALL_CAPS → keep all\n\n### Recent Changes (Iteration 6 & 7 attempts)\n\nIteration 6 added continuation join protection to prevent prefix singles from killing the complete join. This fixed cases like ARAYES SHRAK but introduced regression in Iteration 7 with Polish data (accurate detection of new edge case: intra-recipe headers).\n\n### Absolute File Paths\n\n- **Loop orchestrator:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/title-loop.py`\n- **CLI:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts`\n- **Core implementation:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n- **Unit tests:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts`\n- **Input files:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/` (9 .real.txt files)\n- **Iteration docs:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/{1-7}-{hash}/` (results.txt, feedback.md, improvement-plan.md, committed)\n- **Log:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/iter.txt` (accuracy history)"}],"totalDurationMs":47655,"totalTokens":87591,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1160,"cache_read_input_tokens":84178,"output_tokens":2251,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1160},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
