{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Mec9R64nuL6YcE5gmCxs41","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the historical information. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the title extraction loop iterations.\n\n## Comprehensive Title Extraction Loop History\n\n### Iteration Overview\n\nThe title extraction tool has undergone 7 iterations across 6 months of development, progressing from an initial 16.7% (1/6) pass rate to approximately 50% (4/8) accuracy on the expanded test set. The core algorithm uses embedding-based semantic similarity with multiple heuristic filters to identify recipe titles from OCR'd cookbook text.\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 1 (Initial) — Baseline Failures\n\n**Goal:** Extract recipe titles from OCR'd cookbook pages using embedding similarity.\n\n**Failures:** 5/6 test cases failed (83% failure rate)\n\n**Key issues identified:**\n1. No recipe metadata filtering — lines like `SERVES`, `MAKES`, `PREP TIME` were treated as valid title candidates\n2. No OCR quality gate — garbled text like \"ssekart\", \"DAT FLATBREADS\" passed all filters\n3. Embedding scoring alone couldn't distinguish titles from body text\n4. Position signal was underweighted — titles appeared early but position was only used as tiebreaker\n5. Multi-line title joining was fragile — both partial and complete titles survived, joined incorrectly with `+`\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 2 (404c596) — Proposed Multi-Signal Approach\n\n**Plan:** Five changes targeting metadata filtering, position weighting, OCR quality, and multi-title handling\n\n**What was tried:**\n1. Position-weighted scoring — +0.15 bonus for early candidates\n2. Recipe metadata blocklist — filter `SERVES`, `MAKES`, `PREP TIME`, `BULK FERMENTATION`\n3. OCR quality gate — detect garbled text via vowel ratio, word length, lowercase-start patterns\n4. ALL_CAPS heading bonus — +0.08 bonus for ALL_CAPS text (strong signal in recipe books)\n5. Stricter candidate selection — raise threshold from 60% to 80% of best score; require ALL_CAPS evidence for multi-title output\n\n**Expected impact:** 83% → ~100%\n\n**Actual result:** Iteration 2 was planned but implementation details weren't found in the docs. The plan was sound but the execution moved to iteration 3.\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 3 (a5a0dca) — Refinement After Position Bonus Overreach\n\n**Goal:** Fix failures caused by position bonus being too additive.\n\n**Key insight:** The +0.15 additive position bonus was too aggressive — it allowed low-quality garbled text at position 0 to beat semantically strong titles appearing later.\n\n**What was changed:**\n1. **Inverted substring deduplication** — keep longer candidate instead of shorter (fixes multi-line title joins)\n2. **Position bonus: additive → multiplicative** — ×1.12 factor instead of +0.15 (tiebreaker not replacement)\n3. **Strengthened garble detection** — removed 25-char limit on lowercase-start check; added mid-text sentence boundary detection; improved multi-word garbled fragment detection\n4. **\"First Structural ALL_CAPS Heading\" bonus** — +0.10 to first multi-word ALL_CAPS heading with ≥4-letter words (filters OCR truncations like \"DAT\")\n\n**Failures after iteration 3:**\n- ARAYES SHRAK → still returned \"ARAYES\" (partial, not full join)\n- Baked Eggs → returned empty (dedup killed both prefix and join)\n- FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS → returned only first title (second title fell below inflated threshold)\n- SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS → returned \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" (missing continuation)\n\n**Root causes of iteration 3 failures:**\n- Substring dedup still inverted for multi-line joins (when rawScore of partial ≥ rawScore of join)\n- Position-factor × threshold interaction: first title's bonuses inflated `bestBaseScore`, raising threshold that second title couldn't pass\n- `firstStructuralHeading` selection was purely positional (first match wins), allowing garbled OCR fragments to claim the slot\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 4 (4ecc581) — Root Cause Diagnosis\n\n**Goal:** Diagnose exact failure mechanisms before implementing fixes.\n\n**Key findings:**\n1. **Dedup \"shorter wins\" destroys valid multi-line joins** — When the first half of a split title is syntactically valid on its own (e.g., \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\"), dedup discards the complete join\n2. **Structural bonus leaks into threshold** — The +0.10 structural bonus for first heading inflates `bestBaseScore`, raising the bar so high that equally-valid second titles fail\n3. **OCR corruption poisons structural heading detection** — A garbled fragment \"FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\" passes `isStructuralHeading` and gets bonus meant for real titles\n\n**Plan proposed but not implemented:**\n- Track candidate origin (`single`, `2-line`, `3-line`)\n- Protect continuation joins from dedup\n- Exclude structural bonus from threshold computation\n- Embedding-quality baseHeading selection (not just positional)\n- OCR truncation penalty\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 5 (218113e) — Changes Not Fully Implemented\n\n**Status:** The iteration 4 plan was partially implemented but critical changes were missing:\n- No `origin` field on candidates\n- `baseHeading` still selected positionally\n- `structuralBonus` still exclusive to `firstStructuralHeading`\n\n**Failures after iteration 5 (same 3 as iteration 4):**\n- Baked Eggs → empty string (dedup killed join, prefix below threshold)\n- Finnish Flatbreads → only first title (second title filtered at threshold step)\n- Saffron Wheat Buns → garbled fragment won\n\n**Root causes unchanged from iteration 4.**\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 6 (8a6c985) — Implementation of Iteration 4 Plan\n\n**Goal:** Finally implement the proposed changes from iteration 4.\n\n**What was implemented:**\n1. **Track `origin` field** — candidates now have `origin: \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\"`\n2. **Continuation join protection** — NEW block removes single-line prefixes of surviving multi-line joins (e.g., removes \"Baked Eggs with Feta...\" when \"Baked Eggs with Feta... & Coriander\" survived)\n3. **Separate threshold from ranking** — new `thresholdScore` field excludes structural bonus, preventing threshold inflation\n4. **Embedding-quality baseHeading selection** — restructured scoring into 2 passes: compute rawScore first, select baseHeading by embedding quality, then apply bonuses\n5. **OCR truncation penalty** — detect structural headings whose significant words are suffixes of other headings' words (e.g., \"FRON\" ← \"SAFFRON\"), apply -0.15 rawScore penalty\n\n**Result: 4/8 passing (50%), 4 failing**\n\n**Failures after iteration 6:**\n1. Baked Eggs → still failing (suffix fragment \"& Coriander\" survives and kills join via dedup)\n2. Saffron Wheat Buns → algorithm produces correct output but evaluation fails due to OCR character mismatch (\"/\" in OCR vs \":\" in expected filename)\n3. **NEW Failure 3: CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** → Returns \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM + WARZYWA I BOCZEK\" (intra-recipe ALL_CAPS section header mistaken for second title)\n4. **NEW Failure 4: Faszerowana papryka** → Returns \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\" (Korean romanization with ALL_CAPS bonus) instead of Polish title first line\n\n**Why new failures emerged:**\nThe iteration 6 changes fixed several embedding/threshold issues, allowing more candidates to survive. But they revealed **structural limitations of the multi-title guard**: it cannot distinguish section headers within a recipe (WARZYWA I BOCZEK = \"Vegetables and Bacon\" section) from actual recipe titles. Similarly, it over-weights ALL_CAPS bonuses vs. position, causing subtitles to beat primary titles.\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 7 (9a83c46) — Edge Case Fixes + Evaluation Bug Discovery\n\n**Goal:** Fix remaining failures with targeted, low-risk changes.\n\n**Key insight:** Two failures are algorithm gaps; two are environmental:\n1. **Baked Eggs** — True algorithm issue: suffix fragment protection needed\n2. **Saffron Wheat Buns** — Evaluation harness bug: \"/\" in OCR vs \":\" in filename (filesystem character substitution)\n3. **CHLEBEK** — Limitation: can't distinguish intra-recipe headers from multi-recipe titles\n4. **Faszerowana papryka** — Limitation: ALL_CAPS bonuses override position for bilingual pages\n\n**What was proposed:**\n1. **Remove suffix fragments from continuation joins** — extend `survivingJoins` logic to also remove suffixes (e.g., \"& Coriander\") when a continuation join survived\n2. **Normalize `/` ↔ `:` in `titles_match`** — evaluation harness fix to account for filesystem character encoding\n3. **Hard disqualification for truncated headings** — set rawScore to -1.0 instead of -0.15 penalty\n\n**Result: Still ~50% on original test set, but fixes are targeted and low-risk**\n\n**Remaining failures:**\n- Baked Eggs + Saffron: fixable with proposed changes\n- CHLEBEK + Faszerowana: structural limitations requiring fundamental redesign (position-aware ALL_CAPS filtering, intra-recipe section header detection)\n\n---\n\n## Persistent Patterns Across All Iterations\n\n### Pattern A: Substring Deduplication Inversions\n- **Manifestation:** Dedup rule \"shorter wins\" destroys complete multi-line title joins\n- **Iterations affected:** 1–7\n- **Root cause:** No distinction between \"title + ingredient run-on\" (where shorter is correct) vs. \"first half of split title + join\" (where longer is correct)\n- **Fixes attempted:** Invert logic (iteration 3), protect continuation joins with prefix removal (iteration 6), extend to suffix removal (iteration 7)\n- **Status:** Partially fixed but not completely solved\n\n### Pattern B: Threshold Inflation by Bonuses\n- **Manifestation:** Structural bonus on first title raises bar so high that second title fails despite equal quality\n- **Iterations affected:** 2–6\n- **Root cause:** Bonuses (structuralBonus +0.10) computed before threshold, inflating the multiplier threshold uses\n- **Fixes attempted:** Separate `thresholdScore` from `baseScore` (iteration 6)\n- **Status:** Fixed for multi-recipe cases where both titles are structural headings\n\n### Pattern C: Position Signal Overreach\n- **Manifestation:** Early garbled text beats semantically superior titles appearing later\n- **Iterations affected:** 1–3\n- **Root cause:** Additive position bonus (+0.15) too large relative to semantic scores\n- **Fixes attempted:** Multiplicative factor (×1.12) instead of additive; reduced from +0.15 to ~0.09 effective\n- **Status:** Fixed\n\n### Pattern D: Garbled OCR Fragments Pass Filters\n- **Manifestation:** \"DAT FLATBREADS\", \"ssekart\", \"FRON WHEAT BUNS\" treated as valid candidates\n- **Iterations affected:** 1–7\n- **Root cause:** Hard filters (length, no measurements) insufficient; `isStructuralHeading` fooled by syntactically valid garbage\n- **Fixes attempted:** Vowel ratio checking, lowercase-start detection, word-length checking, embedding-quality baseHeading selection, truncation penalty, hard disqualification\n- **Status:** Significantly improved but still vulnerable to realistic OCR errors\n\n### Pattern E: Multi-Title Guard Limitations\n- **Manifestation:** Can't distinguish section headers (WARZYWA I BOCZEK = ingredients) from recipe titles\n- **Iterations affected:** 6–7 (emerged after earlier failures fixed)\n- **Root cause:** Assumes all ALL_CAPS multi-word lines in same category are recipe titles\n- **Fixes attempted:** None proposed (requires fundamental redesign)\n- **Status:** Unfixed, likely requires position-aware filtering or dictionary lookup\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Design Decisions\n\n| Aspect | Evolution | Current Status |\n|--------|-----------|---|\n| **Semantic signal** | Fixed embedding reference phrases | `\"recipe name, dish title, name of the food\"` |\n| **Position weighting** | Additive → multiplicative | ×1.12 multiplier for early candidates |\n| **Metadata filtering** | None → regex blocklist | Filters SERVES, MAKES, BULK FERMENTATION, etc. |\n| **OCR quality** | None → vowel ratio + patterns | Catches lowercase-start, mid-text periods, garbled words |\n| **All-caps bonuses** | None → +0.08 + +0.10 structural | Distributed: +0.08 all caps, +0.06 structural, +0.04 first |\n| **Multi-line joining** | Basic 2–3 line joins | Continuation-aware; protects joins with continuation chars |\n| **Multi-title logic** | Join with `+` | Checks ALL_CAPS evidence; threshold-based filtering |\n| **Candidate pool** | Unbounded | Capped at 25 (top by ALL_CAPS count, then word count) |\n\n---\n\n## Key Lessons & Unresolved Issues\n\n1. **Suffix fragments are still problematic** — Iteration 6 protected prefixes but not suffixes of continuation joins\n2. **Bonuses are hard to balance** — ALL_CAPS and structural bonuses help in 60% of cases but create false positives in bilingual/multi-section recipes\n3. **Position signal alone insufficient** — Semantic similarity needed but embedding reference phrases may be cookbook/language-dependent\n4. **OCR character corruption unavoidable** — \"/\" vs \":\" mismatch unfixable at algorithm level; requires evaluation harness normalization\n5. **Single vs. multi-recipe detection fragile** — No clear structural signal to distinguish genuine multi-recipe pages from single recipes with section headers\n\nThe iteration history reveals a pattern of incremental refinement, where each fix for one failure pattern often reveals a new limitation. The algorithm now handles most \"clean\" OCR cases well but struggles with edge cases involving character substitution, mixed-case titles, and bilingual pages."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4588e9952d2a7b2c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 97951\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 52719</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dda4a6e7-7d44-4b1e-8d84-edc63f9f063b","uuid":"2b50b4b9-7fb5-44a8-939e-310b0884cb4a","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read ALL files in these directories to understand the history of changes and what's been tried:\n- /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/1-404c596/\n- /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/2-072e8fb/\n- /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/3-a5a0dca/\n- /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/4-4ecc581/\n- /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/5-218113e/\n- /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/6-8a6c985/\n- /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/7-9a83c46/\n\nFor each iteration, summarize: what was the improvement plan, what failures existed, what was tried, and what worked/didn't. Focus on patterns of what keeps breaking and what approaches have been attempted.\n\nBe very thorough - read every feedback.md and improvement-plan.md file in each directory.","agentId":"a4588e9952d2a7b2c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the historical information. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the title extraction loop iterations.\n\n## Comprehensive Title Extraction Loop History\n\n### Iteration Overview\n\nThe title extraction tool has undergone 7 iterations across 6 months of development, progressing from an initial 16.7% (1/6) pass rate to approximately 50% (4/8) accuracy on the expanded test set. The core algorithm uses embedding-based semantic similarity with multiple heuristic filters to identify recipe titles from OCR'd cookbook text.\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 1 (Initial) — Baseline Failures\n\n**Goal:** Extract recipe titles from OCR'd cookbook pages using embedding similarity.\n\n**Failures:** 5/6 test cases failed (83% failure rate)\n\n**Key issues identified:**\n1. No recipe metadata filtering — lines like `SERVES`, `MAKES`, `PREP TIME` were treated as valid title candidates\n2. No OCR quality gate — garbled text like \"ssekart\", \"DAT FLATBREADS\" passed all filters\n3. Embedding scoring alone couldn't distinguish titles from body text\n4. Position signal was underweighted — titles appeared early but position was only used as tiebreaker\n5. Multi-line title joining was fragile — both partial and complete titles survived, joined incorrectly with `+`\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 2 (404c596) — Proposed Multi-Signal Approach\n\n**Plan:** Five changes targeting metadata filtering, position weighting, OCR quality, and multi-title handling\n\n**What was tried:**\n1. Position-weighted scoring — +0.15 bonus for early candidates\n2. Recipe metadata blocklist — filter `SERVES`, `MAKES`, `PREP TIME`, `BULK FERMENTATION`\n3. OCR quality gate — detect garbled text via vowel ratio, word length, lowercase-start patterns\n4. ALL_CAPS heading bonus — +0.08 bonus for ALL_CAPS text (strong signal in recipe books)\n5. Stricter candidate selection — raise threshold from 60% to 80% of best score; require ALL_CAPS evidence for multi-title output\n\n**Expected impact:** 83% → ~100%\n\n**Actual result:** Iteration 2 was planned but implementation details weren't found in the docs. The plan was sound but the execution moved to iteration 3.\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 3 (a5a0dca) — Refinement After Position Bonus Overreach\n\n**Goal:** Fix failures caused by position bonus being too additive.\n\n**Key insight:** The +0.15 additive position bonus was too aggressive — it allowed low-quality garbled text at position 0 to beat semantically strong titles appearing later.\n\n**What was changed:**\n1. **Inverted substring deduplication** — keep longer candidate instead of shorter (fixes multi-line title joins)\n2. **Position bonus: additive → multiplicative** — ×1.12 factor instead of +0.15 (tiebreaker not replacement)\n3. **Strengthened garble detection** — removed 25-char limit on lowercase-start check; added mid-text sentence boundary detection; improved multi-word garbled fragment detection\n4. **\"First Structural ALL_CAPS Heading\" bonus** — +0.10 to first multi-word ALL_CAPS heading with ≥4-letter words (filters OCR truncations like \"DAT\")\n\n**Failures after iteration 3:**\n- ARAYES SHRAK → still returned \"ARAYES\" (partial, not full join)\n- Baked Eggs → returned empty (dedup killed both prefix and join)\n- FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS → returned only first title (second title fell below inflated threshold)\n- SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS → returned \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" (missing continuation)\n\n**Root causes of iteration 3 failures:**\n- Substring dedup still inverted for multi-line joins (when rawScore of partial ≥ rawScore of join)\n- Position-factor × threshold interaction: first title's bonuses inflated `bestBaseScore`, raising threshold that second title couldn't pass\n- `firstStructuralHeading` selection was purely positional (first match wins), allowing garbled OCR fragments to claim the slot\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 4 (4ecc581) — Root Cause Diagnosis\n\n**Goal:** Diagnose exact failure mechanisms before implementing fixes.\n\n**Key findings:**\n1. **Dedup \"shorter wins\" destroys valid multi-line joins** — When the first half of a split title is syntactically valid on its own (e.g., \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\"), dedup discards the complete join\n2. **Structural bonus leaks into threshold** — The +0.10 structural bonus for first heading inflates `bestBaseScore`, raising the bar so high that equally-valid second titles fail\n3. **OCR corruption poisons structural heading detection** — A garbled fragment \"FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)\" passes `isStructuralHeading` and gets bonus meant for real titles\n\n**Plan proposed but not implemented:**\n- Track candidate origin (`single`, `2-line`, `3-line`)\n- Protect continuation joins from dedup\n- Exclude structural bonus from threshold computation\n- Embedding-quality baseHeading selection (not just positional)\n- OCR truncation penalty\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 5 (218113e) — Changes Not Fully Implemented\n\n**Status:** The iteration 4 plan was partially implemented but critical changes were missing:\n- No `origin` field on candidates\n- `baseHeading` still selected positionally\n- `structuralBonus` still exclusive to `firstStructuralHeading`\n\n**Failures after iteration 5 (same 3 as iteration 4):**\n- Baked Eggs → empty string (dedup killed join, prefix below threshold)\n- Finnish Flatbreads → only first title (second title filtered at threshold step)\n- Saffron Wheat Buns → garbled fragment won\n\n**Root causes unchanged from iteration 4.**\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 6 (8a6c985) — Implementation of Iteration 4 Plan\n\n**Goal:** Finally implement the proposed changes from iteration 4.\n\n**What was implemented:**\n1. **Track `origin` field** — candidates now have `origin: \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\"`\n2. **Continuation join protection** — NEW block removes single-line prefixes of surviving multi-line joins (e.g., removes \"Baked Eggs with Feta...\" when \"Baked Eggs with Feta... & Coriander\" survived)\n3. **Separate threshold from ranking** — new `thresholdScore` field excludes structural bonus, preventing threshold inflation\n4. **Embedding-quality baseHeading selection** — restructured scoring into 2 passes: compute rawScore first, select baseHeading by embedding quality, then apply bonuses\n5. **OCR truncation penalty** — detect structural headings whose significant words are suffixes of other headings' words (e.g., \"FRON\" ← \"SAFFRON\"), apply -0.15 rawScore penalty\n\n**Result: 4/8 passing (50%), 4 failing**\n\n**Failures after iteration 6:**\n1. Baked Eggs → still failing (suffix fragment \"& Coriander\" survives and kills join via dedup)\n2. Saffron Wheat Buns → algorithm produces correct output but evaluation fails due to OCR character mismatch (\"/\" in OCR vs \":\" in expected filename)\n3. **NEW Failure 3: CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** → Returns \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM + WARZYWA I BOCZEK\" (intra-recipe ALL_CAPS section header mistaken for second title)\n4. **NEW Failure 4: Faszerowana papryka** → Returns \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\" (Korean romanization with ALL_CAPS bonus) instead of Polish title first line\n\n**Why new failures emerged:**\nThe iteration 6 changes fixed several embedding/threshold issues, allowing more candidates to survive. But they revealed **structural limitations of the multi-title guard**: it cannot distinguish section headers within a recipe (WARZYWA I BOCZEK = \"Vegetables and Bacon\" section) from actual recipe titles. Similarly, it over-weights ALL_CAPS bonuses vs. position, causing subtitles to beat primary titles.\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 7 (9a83c46) — Edge Case Fixes + Evaluation Bug Discovery\n\n**Goal:** Fix remaining failures with targeted, low-risk changes.\n\n**Key insight:** Two failures are algorithm gaps; two are environmental:\n1. **Baked Eggs** — True algorithm issue: suffix fragment protection needed\n2. **Saffron Wheat Buns** — Evaluation harness bug: \"/\" in OCR vs \":\" in filename (filesystem character substitution)\n3. **CHLEBEK** — Limitation: can't distinguish intra-recipe headers from multi-recipe titles\n4. **Faszerowana papryka** — Limitation: ALL_CAPS bonuses override position for bilingual pages\n\n**What was proposed:**\n1. **Remove suffix fragments from continuation joins** — extend `survivingJoins` logic to also remove suffixes (e.g., \"& Coriander\") when a continuation join survived\n2. **Normalize `/` ↔ `:` in `titles_match`** — evaluation harness fix to account for filesystem character encoding\n3. **Hard disqualification for truncated headings** — set rawScore to -1.0 instead of -0.15 penalty\n\n**Result: Still ~50% on original test set, but fixes are targeted and low-risk**\n\n**Remaining failures:**\n- Baked Eggs + Saffron: fixable with proposed changes\n- CHLEBEK + Faszerowana: structural limitations requiring fundamental redesign (position-aware ALL_CAPS filtering, intra-recipe section header detection)\n\n---\n\n## Persistent Patterns Across All Iterations\n\n### Pattern A: Substring Deduplication Inversions\n- **Manifestation:** Dedup rule \"shorter wins\" destroys complete multi-line title joins\n- **Iterations affected:** 1–7\n- **Root cause:** No distinction between \"title + ingredient run-on\" (where shorter is correct) vs. \"first half of split title + join\" (where longer is correct)\n- **Fixes attempted:** Invert logic (iteration 3), protect continuation joins with prefix removal (iteration 6), extend to suffix removal (iteration 7)\n- **Status:** Partially fixed but not completely solved\n\n### Pattern B: Threshold Inflation by Bonuses\n- **Manifestation:** Structural bonus on first title raises bar so high that second title fails despite equal quality\n- **Iterations affected:** 2–6\n- **Root cause:** Bonuses (structuralBonus +0.10) computed before threshold, inflating the multiplier threshold uses\n- **Fixes attempted:** Separate `thresholdScore` from `baseScore` (iteration 6)\n- **Status:** Fixed for multi-recipe cases where both titles are structural headings\n\n### Pattern C: Position Signal Overreach\n- **Manifestation:** Early garbled text beats semantically superior titles appearing later\n- **Iterations affected:** 1–3\n- **Root cause:** Additive position bonus (+0.15) too large relative to semantic scores\n- **Fixes attempted:** Multiplicative factor (×1.12) instead of additive; reduced from +0.15 to ~0.09 effective\n- **Status:** Fixed\n\n### Pattern D: Garbled OCR Fragments Pass Filters\n- **Manifestation:** \"DAT FLATBREADS\", \"ssekart\", \"FRON WHEAT BUNS\" treated as valid candidates\n- **Iterations affected:** 1–7\n- **Root cause:** Hard filters (length, no measurements) insufficient; `isStructuralHeading` fooled by syntactically valid garbage\n- **Fixes attempted:** Vowel ratio checking, lowercase-start detection, word-length checking, embedding-quality baseHeading selection, truncation penalty, hard disqualification\n- **Status:** Significantly improved but still vulnerable to realistic OCR errors\n\n### Pattern E: Multi-Title Guard Limitations\n- **Manifestation:** Can't distinguish section headers (WARZYWA I BOCZEK = ingredients) from recipe titles\n- **Iterations affected:** 6–7 (emerged after earlier failures fixed)\n- **Root cause:** Assumes all ALL_CAPS multi-word lines in same category are recipe titles\n- **Fixes attempted:** None proposed (requires fundamental redesign)\n- **Status:** Unfixed, likely requires position-aware filtering or dictionary lookup\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Design Decisions\n\n| Aspect | Evolution | Current Status |\n|--------|-----------|---|\n| **Semantic signal** | Fixed embedding reference phrases | `\"recipe name, dish title, name of the food\"` |\n| **Position weighting** | Additive → multiplicative | ×1.12 multiplier for early candidates |\n| **Metadata filtering** | None → regex blocklist | Filters SERVES, MAKES, BULK FERMENTATION, etc. |\n| **OCR quality** | None → vowel ratio + patterns | Catches lowercase-start, mid-text periods, garbled words |\n| **All-caps bonuses** | None → +0.08 + +0.10 structural | Distributed: +0.08 all caps, +0.06 structural, +0.04 first |\n| **Multi-line joining** | Basic 2–3 line joins | Continuation-aware; protects joins with continuation chars |\n| **Multi-title logic** | Join with `+` | Checks ALL_CAPS evidence; threshold-based filtering |\n| **Candidate pool** | Unbounded | Capped at 25 (top by ALL_CAPS count, then word count) |\n\n---\n\n## Key Lessons & Unresolved Issues\n\n1. **Suffix fragments are still problematic** — Iteration 6 protected prefixes but not suffixes of continuation joins\n2. **Bonuses are hard to balance** — ALL_CAPS and structural bonuses help in 60% of cases but create false positives in bilingual/multi-section recipes\n3. **Position signal alone insufficient** — Semantic similarity needed but embedding reference phrases may be cookbook/language-dependent\n4. **OCR character corruption unavoidable** — \"/\" vs \":\" mismatch unfixable at algorithm level; requires evaluation harness normalization\n5. **Single vs. multi-recipe detection fragile** — No clear structural signal to distinguish genuine multi-recipe pages from single recipes with section headers\n\nThe iteration history reveals a pattern of incremental refinement, where each fix for one failure pattern often reveals a new limitation. The algorithm now handles most \"clean\" OCR cases well but struggles with edge cases involving character substitution, mixed-case titles, and bilingual pages."}],"totalDurationMs":52719,"totalTokens":97951,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12373,"cache_read_input_tokens":82069,"output_tokens":3503,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":12373},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
