{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01E5pWH4YKanFsy4LYTrUywR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me outline my proposed approach before writing the plan.\n\n**Key proposed changes:**\n\n1. **Failure 1 & 4B (continuation joins fragile):** Pre-merge continuation lines before candidate generation. If line N+1 starts with `&/+:/(`, merge it into line N at the line-processing stage, so the merged text becomes a single candidate. This eliminates the entire chain of fragility: the join doesn't need to survive thresholds, pre-filters, or dedup independently.\n\n2. **Failure 2 (intra-recipe section headers):** Add ingredient-gap detection to the multi-title guard. When multiple ALL_CAPS headings survive, check if lines between them contain ingredient patterns (measurements, numbers). If yes, later headings are section sub-headers within the same recipe — keep only the first.\n\n3. **Failure 3 (ALL_CAPS subtitle overrides first-line title):** Add first-line mixed-case title protection. When a mixed-case candidate at line 0 passes the embedding threshold and the only ALL_CAPS candidate immediately follows it (line 1), treat the ALL_CAPS as a subtitle/transliteration — prefer position 0.\n\n4. **Failure 4A (OCR separator mismatch):** This is an eval harness issue, not an algorithm issue. Note it but propose no code change in `lib/text-classifier/`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6666,"cache_read_input_tokens":34818,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6666},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dda4a6e7-7d44-4b1e-8d84-edc63f9f063b","uuid":"8186d9ad-0838-42d2-99ce-aa11e1f1f4f9"}
